President Obama has announced a Presidential Delegation to attend the Canonization of Mother Teresa in Vatican City on September 4, 2016. The delegation will be led by Lisa Monaco, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism. Other members of the delegation include Kenneth Hackett, U.S. Ambassador to the Holy See, Suzy George, Deputy Assistant to the President and Executive Secretary and Chief of Staff at the National Security Council, Sister Donna J. Markham OP, Ph.D., President and CEO of Catholic Charities USA, and Dr. Carolyn Y. Woo, President and CEO of Catholic Relief Services.